.TH POOL_BRIDGE 8 "2025" "POOL Protocol" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
pool_bridge \- TCP to POOL protocol bridge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pool_bridge
.I mode
.I args...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pool_bridge
provides transparent bridging between TCP connections and POOL sessions.
This enables legacy TCP applications to communicate over POOL without
modification.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B tcp2pool \fItcp_port pool_ip pool_port\fR
Listen for TCP connections on
.I tcp_port
and forward each to a POOL session at
.IR pool_ip:pool_port .
.TP
.B pool2tcp \fIpool_port tcp_ip tcp_port\fR
Listen for POOL sessions on
.I pool_port
and forward each to a TCP connection at
.IR tcp_ip:tcp_port .
.SH EXAMPLES
Bridge local port 8080 to POOL peer at 10.0.0.2:9253:
.RS
.B pool_bridge tcp2pool 8080 10.0.0.2 9253
.RE
.PP
Receive POOL sessions and forward to local HTTP server:
.RS
.B pool_bridge pool2tcp 9253 127.0.0.1 80
.RE
.SH THREAD MODEL
Each bridged connection gets a dedicated worker thread with bidirectional
data relay. Maximum concurrent bridges is configurable (default: 64).
